    dc:title "Three new enchytraeid species (Enchytraeidae, Annelida) from mountain soils of Korea and ten species new for the country" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4358992>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4359016>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4359020> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4358992>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Cognettia koreana sp. n. (A, B), Henlea bidiverticulata sp. n. (C) and Mesenchytraeus longidiverticulatus sp. n. (D–F). C. koreana sp. n.: A. Sperm funnel. B. Spermatheca. H. bidiverticulata sp. n.: C. Segments IV–IX (p=pharyngeal glands, s=spermatheca, id=intestinal diverticula, dv=dorsal blood vessel). M. longidiverticulatus sp. n.: D. Spermatheca. E. Segments III–VIII (specimen with three spermatheca 1.s=first spermatheca, 2.s=second spermatheca, 3.s=third spermatheca, pharyngeal glands marked with grey colour). F. Atrium with atrial glands and penial bulb with small penial glands and some accessory copulatory glands. Scale bars 50 μm, C and E 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4358992/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4359016>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Micrographs of Mesenchytraeus longidiverticulatus sp. n. A. Brain. B. Clitellar glands, lateral view. C. Clitellar glands, dorsal view. D. Clitellar glands, ventral view (penial bulbs marked with arrows). E. Head pore (marked with white arrow, brain marked with black arrow). F. Ventral chaetae in V–VII. G. Densely aggregated epidermal glands. H. Coelomocytes. I. Segments X–XII (sperm funnels marked with black arrows, atrial glands marked with white arrows). J–L. Sperm funnel. A–B, G–L in vivo, E fixed, stained, C–D, F fixed, not stained. Scale bars 50 μm. (C–D, paratype slide 2595; F, paratype slide 2596)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4359016/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4359020>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Micrographs of Mesenchytraeus longidiverticulatus sp. n. A. Segments XI–XIII (sf=sperm funnels, a=atrium, b=bursa, ag=atrial gland). B–D. Penial bulbs (a=atrium, b=bursa, here atrial glands marked with black arrows, *=origin of atrial glands, accessory glands marked with white arrows). E. Sperm rolls in sperm sac. F–J. Spermathecae (a=ampulla, ed=ental duct, ectal duct marked with white arrows, diverticula marked with black arrows). K. Spermathecal ectal duct at orifice with strong cuticular covering. A–E, G–K in vivo, F fixed, not stained. Scale bars 50 μm. (F, holotype)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4359020/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

